Functions used in DATE and TIME 

-- DATE Functions
1. CURDATE() - retuns the current DATE
2. CURRENT_DATE() - Synonym of CURDATE()
3. DATE(expr) - extracts the date part of a datetime expression
4. DATE_ADD(date,INTERVAL expr unit) - Adds an interval to a date where expr can be YEAR,MONTH,or DAY
5. DATE_DIFF(date1,date2) - retuns the number of days between two dates
6. DAY(daye)/DAYOFMONTH(date) - retuns the day of the month(1-31)
7. DAYNAME(date) - retuns the name of the weekday
8. DAYOFWEEK(date) - retuns the weekday index(1=sunday, 7=saturday)
9. DAYOFYEAR(date) - retuns the day of the year(1-366)
10. LAST_DAY(date)  - returns the last day of the month for the given date
11. MONTH(date) - retuns the month(1-12)
12. MONTHNAME(date) - retuns the name of the month
13. YEAR(date) - retuns the year
14. QUARTER(date) - retuns the quarter of the year(1-4)
15. TO_DAYS(date) - retuns the number of days since year 0.
16. FROM_DAYS(number) - retuns date value corresponding to that day count

-- TIME Functions
1. CURTIME() - retuns the current
2. CURRENT_TIME() - Synonym for CURTIME()
3. ADDTIME(expr1,expr2) - add a time interval to a time/datetime.
4. SUBTIME(expr1,expre2) - subtracts a time interval
5. SEC_TO_TIME(seconds) - converts second to standard time format
6. TIME(expr) - extracts the time part of a datetime expression.
7. TIME_TO_SEC(time) - converts a time value into seconds.
8. HOUR(time) - retruns the hour(0-23)
9. MINUTE(time) - returns the minute(0-59)
10. SECOND(time) - return the second(0-59)

-- Combined DateTime Functions
1. NOW() - retuns current date and time
2. CURRENT_TIMESTAMP()- Synonym fo NOW()
3. LOCALTIME()/LOCALTIMESTAMP()- Synonym for NOW()
4. UNIX_TIMESTAMP() - returns the Unix timestamp(seconds since 1970-01-01)
5. FROM_UNIXTIME(unix_timestamp) - converts unix timestamp to date/time
6. STR_TO_DATE(str,format) - Formats a date/time according to a format string.
7. EXTRACT(unit FROM date) - extracts a part of a date (year,month,day,etc)
8. MAKEDATE(year,dayofyear) - creates a date from year and day-of-year.
9. MAKETIME(hour,minute,second) - creates a time from hour, minute and second
10. TIMESTAMP(expr) - converts an expression to a timestamp.
11. TIMESTAMPADD(unit,interval,datetime) - adds an interval to a datetime
12. TIMESTAMPDIFF(unit,datetime1,datetime2) - retuns the difference between two datetimes in the given unit

-- WEEK Functions
1. WEEK(date,mode) - returns the week number of a date.
2. WEEKDAY(date) - returns the weekday index(0(monday)-6(sunday))
3. WEEKOFYEAR(date) - retuns the week number (1-53) of the year.